================================================================================
HYPLAN — IMPROVEMENT IDEAS
================================================================================

--- PACKAGE-WIDE ---
* Consistent logging configuration across all modules (some still use basicConfig)
* Add type stubs or py.typed marker for downstream IDE support
* Publish to PyPI / conda-forge
* Add CLI entry point for common tasks (generate flight lines, export plan)
* Increase test coverage — many modules have no dedicated test file

--- POSSIBLE NEW MODULES ---

export.py:
* Consolidated export module for flight plans and lines
* Export to TrackAir format
* Export to KML (flight lines, swath polygons, full plans)
* Export to GeoJSON (flight lines with metadata)
* Export to CSV / Excel for field team use
* Import flight lines from KML / shapefile

weather.py:
* API for GMAO forecast data
* Wind data for wind barbs on map
* Real-time cloud / visibility forecasts
* Time-on-deck (TOD) predictions for data collection windows

gui.py (interactive planning tool):
* Map-based line selection with box or ad hoc polygon
* Hover to reveal solar elevation rise/set times
* Copy / delete / rotate / nudge individual lines
* Draw a polygon and generate flight lines interactively
* Aircraft icons on map
* Wind barbs overlay

--- EXISTING MODULES ---

units.py:
* Support angular units (degrees, radians) in conversion helpers
* Add time unit conversions (seconds, minutes, hours)

geometry.py:
* Regionate geometries by UTM zone for large study areas
* Get time zone from lat/lon
* Add polygon area calculation in metric units

flight_line.py:
* Curved flight lines for glint / CH4 mapping
* Spiral flight patterns
* Multi-point flight lines (> 2 vertices)
* Merge adjacent collinear flight lines

flight_box.py:
* Accept target GSD as input instead of raw overlap percentage
* Return daily_lines grouping from optimizer-aware box generation

flight_plan.py:
* Account for wind in transit time estimates
* Add fuel burn estimation per segment
* Support multiple altitude levels within a single plan
* Export plan as pilot-ready briefing sheet

flight_optimizer.py:
* Replace greedy heuristic with 2-opt or simulated annealing
* Return daily_lines grouping directly in result dict
* Support time-window constraints (e.g., solar elevation, satellite overpass)
* Multi-aircraft scheduling
* Weight graph edges by fuel burn in addition to time

dubins_path.py:
* 3D Dubins paths (climb/descent during turns)
* Compare 2D vs 3D Dubins output and performance
* Wind-corrected Dubins paths

aircraft.py:
* Altitude-dependent fuel burn model
* Weight-dependent performance (payload vs range tradeoff)
* Turboprop vs jet engine modeling differences

airports.py:
* Cache downloaded CSV data to avoid re-downloading
* Add fuel availability and FBO information
* Filter by airport services (hangars, maintenance)

sensors.py:
* Spectral band metadata (wavelength ranges, bit depth)
* Add more sensor implementations 
* Sensor data rate estimation for storage planning

frame_camera.py:
* Support oblique viewing angles
* Stereo coverage planning (forward/nadir/backward)

lvis.py:
* Model shot density vs ground speed
* Swath width variation with scan pattern

radar.py:
* Interferometric SAR baseline planning
* Near/far range incidence angle maps

swath.py:
* Calculate ground pixel size along a flight line
* Plot swath colored by ground pixel size
* 2D cross-section plot with terrain profile and swath geometry
* Swath gap/overlap analysis between adjacent lines

sun.py:
* Integrate with flight_optimizer for solar-constrained scheduling

glint.py:
* Calculate percentage of line exceeding a glint angle threshold
* Map predicted glint intensity along flight lines
* Glint avoidance routing

clouds.py:
* Support non-GEE cloud data sources (ERA5, MERRA-2)
* Probabilistic clear-sky forecasting for campaign scheduling

terrain.py:
* Support additional DEM sources (Copernicus GLO-30, ASTER GDEM)
* Terrain slope / aspect maps for study area characterization
* Obstacle clearance analysis along flight path

satellites.py:
* Multi-satellite coordinated overpass planning
* Satellite revisit frequency maps for a study area
* Underfly timing optimization (aircraft + satellite coincidence)

plotting.py:
* 3D flight trajectory visualization
* Animated flight plan playback
* Side-by-side multi-day plan comparison
* Export figures to publication-quality formats
